Chingola – A 53-year-old woman, Tisa Nkandu of Kasompe township in Chingola district in Zambia’s Copperbelt area, has been murdered by her husband following a marital dispute over relish, the Zambian Observer reported on Tuesday. Copperbelt Commissioner of Police Charity Katanga confirmed the incident, saying the deceased sustained a deep cut in the head and a sharp instrument is believed to have been used in the act. She said the suspect Joseph Siavulwe, 53, had since been arrested and was in police custody. * Receive IOL's top stories via Whatsapp by sending your name to 0745573535. African News Agency (ANA)